Segun Olaniyan Katsina – Governor Aminu Bello Masari of Katsina State has expressed sadness over the death of former (Second Republic) President and Turakin Sokoto, Alhaji Shehu Usman Shagari. Masari in a statement made by his  media aide, Abdu Labaran on Saturday, said Nigeria has lost one of its last standing great statesmen. The Governor described the late leader as one of the leading conscience of the nation, who lived an exemplary life defined by uncommon simplicity. “Former President Shehu Shagari was a rare gem, and his death has created a wide leadership chasm that may take a long time to fill”. “His death is particularly devastating coming at a time when our nation, buffeted by multifaceted challenges, requires his wise counsel”.